# CODEOWNERS — auto-request review on protected paths.
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Workflow + deploy config: only the repo owner can change these.
# Combined with branch protection requiring code-owner review on main,
# this prevents an attacker who lands a malicious PR from modifying CI
# to exfiltrate the AZURE_STATIC_WEB_APPS_API_TOKEN.
/.github/workflows/    @terencetsakiris
/.github/CODEOWNERS    @terencetsakiris
/staticwebapp.config.json  @terencetsakiris

# package-lock.json defines the supply chain reaching the build runner;
# malicious lockfile edits could pull in compromised packages.
/package-lock.json     @terencetsakiris
/package.json          @terencetsakiris
